graphs
Class Node

java.lang.Object
  graphs.Node
Direct Known Subclasses:
ForcedNode
public class Node
extends java.lang.Object

A node is an element that is subject to be in a group. In microarray data bicluster analysis, samples (nucleotide sequences, genes) and conditions (experimental conditions patients) biclustered at least once are expected to be Nodes.

Author:
Rodrigo Santamaría
